{"name":"Kerkyra (True)","size":"huge","type":"aberration","tag":"Aboleth","alignment":"Lawful Evil","hitDice":"32","armorName":"natural armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":12,"otherArmorDesc":"17 (natural armor)","speed":"10","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"40","hover":true,"swimSpeed":"40","customHP":false,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"336 (32d12 + 128)","speedDesc":"10 ft., swim 40 ft.","strPoints":"21","dexPoints":"9","conPoints":"18","intPoints":"24","wisPoints":"17","chaPoints":"20","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"120","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":120,"cr":"23","customCr":"10 (5,900 XP)","customProf":4,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"Kerkyra (True) can take 3 legendary actions, choosing from the options below. Only one legendary action option can be used at a time and only at the end of another creature's turn. Kerkyra (True) regains spent legendary actions at the start of her turn.","isLair":true,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside her lair, Kerkyra (True) can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), Kerkyra (True) can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"Kerkyra (True) can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and she can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isRegional":true,"regionalDescription":"The region containing Kerkyra (True)'s lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If Kerkyra (True) dies, the first two effects fade over the course of [3d10] days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Amphibious","desc":"Kerkyra (True) can breathe air and water."},{"name":"Mucous Cloud","desc":"While underwater, Kerkyra (True) is surrounded by transformative mucus. A creature that touches Kerkyra (True) or that hits her with a melee attack while within 5 ft. of her must make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failure, the creature is diseased for [1d4] hours. The diseased creature can breathe only underwater."},{"name":"Probing Telepathy","desc":"If a creature communicates telepathically with Kerkyra (True), Kerkyra (True) learns the creature's greatest desires if Kerkyra (True) can see the creature."},{"name":"Innate Spellcasting (Psionics)","desc":"Kerkyra (True)'s innate spellcasting ability is Intelligence (spell save DC [INT SAVE], [INT ATK] to hit with spell attacks). She can innately cast the following spells, requiring no material components:\n\n> At will: _command, mind spike, telekinesis_\n> 3/day each: _dominate beast/monster/person, hold monster/person, invisibility_\n> 1/day each: _mind blank, psychic scream_"}],"actions":[{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"Kerkyra (True) makes four tentacle attacks and one tail attack."},{"name":"Tentacle","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 3d6] bludgeoning damage. If the target is a creature, it must succeed on a DC 14 Constitution saving throw or become diseased. The disease has no effect for 1 minute and can be removed by any magic that cures disease. After 1 minute, the diseased creature's skin becomes translucent and slimy, the creature can't regain hit points unless it is underwater, and the disease can be removed only by Heal or another disease-curing spell of 6th level or higher. When the creature is outside a body of water, it takes [1d12] acid damage every 10 minutes unless moisture is applied to the skin before 10 minutes have passed."},{"name":"Tail","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 10 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 4d6] bludgeoning damage."},{"name":"Enslave (3/day)","desc":"Kerkyra (True) targets one creature she can see within 30 ft. of her. The target must succeed on a DC 14 Wisdom saving throw or be magically charmed by Kerkyra (True) until Kerkyra (True) dies or until she is on a different plane of existence from the target. The charmed target is under Kerkyra (True)'s control and can't take reactions, and Kerkyra (True) and the target can communicate telepathically with each other over any distance.\nWhenever the charmed target takes damage, the target can repeat the saving throw. On a success, the effect ends. No more than once every 24 hours, the target can also repeat the saving throw when it is at least 1 mile away from Kerkyra (True)."}],"reactions":[],"legendaries":[{"name":"Detect","desc":"Kerkyra (True) makes a Wisdom (Perception) check."},{"name":"Tail Swipe","desc":"Kerkyra (True) makes one tail attack."},{"name":"Psychic Drain (Costs 2 Actions)","desc":"One creature charmed by Kerkyra (True) takes [3d6] psychic damage, and Kerkyra (True) regains hit points equal to the damage the creature takes."}],"lairs":[{"name":"Hands Everywhere","desc":"Kerkyra (True) casts Phantasmal Force (no components required) on any number of creatures she can see within 60 feet of her. While maintaining concentration on this effect, Kerkyra (True) can't take other lair actions. If a target succeeds on the saving throw or if the effect ends for it, the target is immune to Kerkyra (True)'s phantasmal force lair action for the next 24 hours, although such a creature can choose to be affected."},{"name":"Raging Pools","desc":"Pools of water within 90 feet of Kerkyra (True) surge outward in a grasping tide. Any creature on the ground within 20 feet of such a pool must succeed on a DC 14 Strength saving throw or be pulled up to 20 feet into the water and knocked prone. Kerkyra (True) can't use this lair action again until she has used a different one."},{"name":"Psychic Tides","desc":"Water in Kerkyra (True)'s lair magically becomes a conduit for the creature's rage. Kerkyra (True) can target any number of creatures she can see in such water within 90 feet of her. A target must succeed on a DC 14 Wisdom saving throw or take [2d6] psychic damage. Kerkyra (True) can't use this lair action again until she has used a different one."}],"regionals":[{"name":"Tainted Aura","desc":"The skies within 6 miles of the lair are blackened by Kerkyra (True)'s presence. Sunlight cannot fall within this region, and Kerkyra (True) can choose to change the brightness anywhere from dim light to pitch black."},{"name":"Tainted Waters","desc":"Water sources within 1 mile of the lair are supernaturally fouled. Enemies of Kerkyra (True) that drink such water vomit it within minutes."},{"name":"Mirror Mirror","desc":"As an action, Kerkyra (True) can create an illusory image of herself within 1 mile of the lair. The copy can appear at any location Kerkyra (True) has seen before or in any location a creature charmed by Kerkyra (True) can currently see. Once created, the image lasts for as long as Kerkyra (True) maintains concentration, as if concentrating on a spell. Although the image is intangible, it looks, sounds, and can move like Kerkyra (True). Kerkyra (True) can sense, speak, and use telepathy from the image's position as if present at that position. If the image takes any damage, it disappears."}],"sthrows":[{"name":"con","order":2},{"name":"int","order":3},{"name":"wis","order":4}],"skills":[{"name":"arcana","stat":"int"},{"name":"history","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"perception","stat":"wis","note":" (ex)"},{"name":"religion","stat":"int","note":" (ex)"}],"damagetypes":[{"name":"psychic","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"}],"specialdamage":[{"name":"bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical attacks","note":" (Immune)","type":"i"}],"conditions":[],"languages":[{"name":"All","speaks":true}],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":8,"damage":[],"pluralName":"","bonusActions":[],"mythics":[{"name":"Tides of the Old Moon","desc":"Kerkyra (True) calls forth all water within 3 miles of her to her current location, taking up to 3 turns to arrive. While the water travels to her, it can destroy nearly anything in its path to get closer to her. As the water arrives to her location, she controls it in a sphere around her, and this sphere acts as her lair."}],"isMythic":true,"mythicDescription":"If Kerkyra (True)'s mythic trait is active, she can use the options below as legendary actions for 1 hour after using Rage of the Ancients."}